{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Toast Thai sticky rice in a frying pan for 5-10 minutes until golden brown.","Place toasted rice in mixing bowl and grind <nobr>1 min\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Transfer to a small bowl and set aside.","Place chicken in mixing bowl then mince <nobr>2 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Transfer to a small bowl and set aside.","Place water, ginger, garlic, salt and pepper in mixing bowl then cook <nobr>4 min\/100°C\/speed <\/nobr>.","Add reserved minced chicken then cook <nobr>4 min\/100°C\/\/speed <\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and stir and release any chicken from blade then cook again <nobr>4 min\/100°C\/\/speed <\/nobr>. Drain chicken using simmering basket and discard ginger and garlic.","Place shallots, spring onions, coriander, leaves from 2 mint sprigs, fish sauce, lime juice, chilli powder and sugar in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add reserved drained chicken and remaining mint leaves then mix <nobr>10 sec\/\/speed 2<\/nobr> .","Arrange on little gem lettuce leaves on a platter with sliced cucumber and bean sprouts then sprinkle with reserved ground sticky rice, to taste, for an authentic nutty flavour."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["20 g Thai sticky rice","400 g chicken breasts, cut in pieces","100 g water","5 g fresh root ginger, cut in round slices (2 mm)","1 garlic clove","1 pinch fine sea salt","1 pinch ground black pepper","80 g shallots, halved","4 spring onions, cut in lengths (2 cm)","4 sprigs fresh coriander, leaves only","4 sprig fresh mint, leaves only","1 Tbsp fish sauce","1 Tbsp lime juice","½ tsp chilli powder","½ tsp sugar","2 little gem lettuce, heads, leaves separated","100 g cucumber, sliced (3 mm)","50 g fresh bean sprouts"]}],"id":"r105065","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-7QlxNVe5J84\/XZQu85vqjkI\/AAAAAAAAcY4\/wWN4VUlQEUgEYaM1RWi8sb1tpfP8CdaLACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_9sXZ5-S0vZAu-0C0.png